---
// Ecosystem section — the connected stack
---

<section class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-sm font-mono text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">
    The Ecosystem
  </h2>

  <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-8 max-w-2xl">
    Four open source projects that work together. Each solves a distinct problem. Together, they form an intelligence layer for AI agent systems.
  </p>

  <!-- Ecosystem diagram -->
  <div class="card p-6 md:p-8 mb-6">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      
      <a href="https://github.com/heybeaux/engram" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="group p-4 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="text-lg">🧠</span>
          <span class="font-mono font-semibold group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Engram</span>
          <span class="tag">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-2">What agents <strong>did</strong>. Persistent memory with semantic search, dream cycle consolidation, and knowledge graphs.</p>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-muted)]">NestJS · PostgreSQL · pgvector · 2,816 tests</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://github.com/heybeaux/acr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="group p-4 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="text-lg">📦</span>
          <span class="font-mono font-semibold group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">ACR</span>
          <span class="tag">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-2">What agents <strong>can do</strong>. Context management that loads the right capabilities at the right resolution. 98% token reduction.</p>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-muted)]">TypeScript · 105 tests · 100% recall · 64.7% precision</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://github.com/heybeaux/awm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="group p-4 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="text-lg">🔮</span>
          <span class="font-mono font-semibold group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">AWM</span>
          <span class="tag">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-2">What agents <strong>will do</strong>. Bayesian prediction + multi-armed bandits for model routing, constraint injection, and cost optimization.</p>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-muted)]">TypeScript · 56 tests · Grade A benchmark · 81.5% prediction accuracy</span>
      </a>

      <div class="group p-4 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] border-dashed">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="text-lg">⚡</span>
          <span class="font-mono font-semibold">Forge</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-muted)] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--color-border)]">Private</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-2">The <strong>orchestration layer</strong>. Multi-agent pipelines with approval workflows, client profiles, and sector-aware agents.</p>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-muted)]">Mastra · Next.js · 92 agents · 143 ACR capabilities</span>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Connection line -->
    <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] text-center font-mono">
        Engram remembers → ACR loads → AWM predicts → Forge executes
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)] text-center mt-2">
        Something new is being built on top of this stack. Stay tuned.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>
